		"purpose": "Canonical reference composition for an operational dashboard, captured 1:1 from the Figma 'Dashboard - Example'. ONE Section contains: a section header (title + description) → a 3-up metric-card row → a Divider → a data table (header row + rows). Assemble new dashboards by following this structure and drawing blocks from dashboard/blocks.json.",
		"source": "Figma file uI6oKmJ0qDhsEuE0nFah2W, node 730:11891 (Dashboard - Example) → frame 730:11892 (Dashboard); block palette 721:6689 (Dashboard - Blocks).",
		"conventions": "Concept Heading/Body. ONE Section wraps the whole dashboard (no zebra of multiple sections). Order: section header → metric row (3 auto equal-height cards) → Divider → data table. Metric card = muted label, large value Heading, Badge + delta note (NO placeholder icon). Section spacing 'small'. Header shows the app name; meta-nav off. The reference toolbar (Selects + icon buttons) and the avatar/progress-bar table cells are omitted — the runtime cannot populate them meaningfully yet, and empty placeholders are forbidden."
	},
